() , ? asked the Prime Minister, Minister of Internal Administration and Deputy Minister of Defence, Public Security, Law and Order, : (a) Is he aware that the allowance paid to the war heroes in the operational service has been increased from Rs. 3000 to Rs. 5000 from the budget for year 2009? (b) Will he inform this House (i) whether that increased amount will be given to the war heroes; and (ii) if so, the date from which it will be given? (c) Will he state the number of war heroes who are entitled to receive the aforesaid amount? (d) If not, why?

() , ? asked the Minister of Transport: (a) Will he inform this House of the number of official vehicles at the head office of the Sri Lanka Transport Board? (b) Is he aware of the fact that vehicles have been obtained by the aforesaid Board on rent basis, from outside and private institutions, for the use of the officials of its head office? (c) Will he submit to this House (i) the number of vehicles so obtained; (ii) the make and registration numbers of those vehicles; (iii) of the officials who use these vehicles; (iv) the institutions or private owners from whom these vehicles have been obtained; (v) their names and addresses; and (vi) the monthly rent paid against those vehicles? (d) Will he state (i) the distance that each of these vehicles has run from January 2008 up to now; (ii) the amount of money paid for that; and (iii) where these vehicles are parked? (e) If not, why?

asked the Minister of Child Development and Womens Empowerment : (a) Will she inform this House of, (i) the number of children who are provided with financial assistance under the Kepakaru Deguru programme in Sri Lanka; and (ii) the amount provided for each child? (b) Will she submit to this House, (i) the number of children who are provided with financial assistance under the Sevana Sarana Foster Parent Scheme, in Sri Lanka; and (ii) the amount provided for each child? (c) Will she state, (i) the measures that have been taken up to now for the extension of the aforesaid projects; (ii) the number of children newly enrolled for the Kepakaru Deguru and Sevana Sarana Foster Parent Scheme in the year 2008? (d) If not, why?

(b) Will he state, (i) the additional benefits given to these heroic forces personnel as at 01st January 2006 and after 17th May 2009; (ii) the number of houses been built and given to the armed force personnel in 2008 and in 2009 to-date; (iii) whether these houses were given on free of charge; (iv) if not the payment terms; and (v) the names of the heroic forces personnel who received these housing benefits? (c) If not, why?

Ravi Karunanayake) Thank you, Hon. Deputy Speaker. We condemn these types of despicable actions and we hold the Government responsible for all this. Only yesterday the Hon. Speaker made a very urgent plea to ensure that we run this House in a more amicable manner. Is this what you are doing? You may have made a mistake when you were in the Chair. That does not mean that you can violate the Standing Orders. This type of nonsense goes on because we have a Secretary-General of Parliament who is on an acting basis. You must understand that there

has to be decorum in this Parliament. We are not bothered about the Deputy Minister; any other Minister can reply. If he does not want to be here, he could have gone for prayers. We did not want him to be here. So, ensure that matters are addressed in the proper manner. Hon. Deputy Speaker, your amiable and generous disposition seems to be somewhat disturbed these days. You are a person whom we basically respect. You should ensure that we are permitted to carry on with this Adjournment Motion. Now, the reason I move this Adjournment Motion is to reveal the state of affairs in the Foreign Ministry. Hon. Deputy Speaker, I move: Foreign Policy is a very important aspect for a progressive Nation. Foreign Policy strategy is one of the best tools to be used to link Sri Lanka to the world. The theory put to practice is implemented through Ambassadors, Officials who are appointed to carry out the task. However, in the recent past the Foreign Ministry has been recruiting many Ambassadors and sidelining many competent people. There is also a very heavy over-run on the cost of the Ministry, resulting in capital expenditure being converted to recurrent expenditure. Therefore, we wish to ask: 1. How many Ambassadors, Deputy Ambassadors, First Secretaries, Second Secretaries, have been posted and recalled within less than two years? 2. How many Embassies are operating without Ambassadors today? 3. Information that is requested in Parliament is not being provided, thus concealing information from the general public. 4. Career Diplomats are being sidelined and political appointees are being appointed thus creating confusion, credibility and de-motivation of the staff of the Ministry. We find the latest trend not to give information to Parliament is becoming the way of the Parliamentary process of the Government now. Therefore, in conclusion we call upon the Government to ensure that a sound, sustainable and practical foreign policy is urgently restored before it deteriorates any further. ( ) (The Hon. Lakshman Kiriella)
